About the problem: Given the probabilities for winning individual dollar amounts from a raffle, determine the expected value of a raffle ticket. Decimal response format. 

The Worked Example can be hidden from veiw by commenting out the <hint> portion of the document.
*************************************************************-->
<problem><title></title>
<setup>
  <select name="p10">
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.05</math>
    </option>
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.10</math>
    </option>
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.15</math>
    </option>
  </select>

  <select name="p5">
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.10</math>
    </option>
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.15</math>
    </option>
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.20</math>
    </option>
  </select>

  <select name="p2">
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.20</math>
    </option>
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.30</math>
    </option>
    <option><math displayDecimals="2" padZeros>0.40</math>
    </option>
  </select>

  <math name="p1" displayDecimals="2" padZeros simplify>1 - $p10 - $p5 - $p2</math>
  <math name="expectedValue" displayDecimals="2" padZeros>10$p10 + 5$p5 + 2$p2 + $p1</math>
</setup>

  
<!--testing-->
<!-- <p>p10 = $p10</p>
<p>p5 = $p5</p>
<p>p2 = $p2</p>
