<!--testing-->

<p>You hold one ticket to a raffle that has the following payouts:</p>

<p>You will win <m>\$ 10</m> with probability <m>$p10</m></p>
<p>You will win <m>\$ 5</m> with probability <m>$p5</m> </p>
<p>You will win <m>\$ 2</m> with probability <m>$p2</m></p>
<p>You will win <m>\$ 1</m> with probability <m>$p1</m></p>

Find the expected value of the amount of money you will win. Do not include the dollar sign in your answer. 

      
<p><m>\text{Expected value} = \$</m>   <answer name="ans14" >
      <mathInput name="userInput" prefillLatex="0.00"/>
      
      <award name="correct" allowedErrorInNumbers="0.1" allowedErrorIsAbsolute credit="1">    
        <when>
      $userInput=$expectedValue
        </when>
      </award>

      <award name="roundingError" allowedErrorInNumbers="1" allowedErrorIsAbsolute credit="0">
        <when>
      $userInput=$expectedValue
        </when>
      </award>
      
      <award name="correctSymbolic" symbolicEquality simplifyOnCompare credit="1">    
        <when>
      $userInput=$expectedValue
        </when>
      </award>

      <award name="tooHigh"  credit="0">    
        <when>
      $userInput > <math>10</math>
        </when>
      </award>

      <award name="tooLow"  credit="0">    
        <when>
      $userInput < <math>1</math>
        </when>
      </award>
    </answer>
  </p>

 
