  <feedback condition="$tooLow">Check again. it is not possible for the expected value to be less than the minimum possible win.</feedback>
  
  <feedback condition="$ans14.numSubmissions > 2 and $ans14.creditAchieved != 1">
     <div name="helpText">
       If a <ref uri="https://open.lib.umn.edu/probability/chapter/topic-2-4/https://open.lib.umn.edu/probability/chapter/topic-2-3/">random variable</ref> <m>X</m>, takes on possible values <m>v_1, v_2, v_3,...</m> which have probabilites <m>p_1, p_2, p_3,...</m> respectively, then the <ref uri="https://open.lib.umn.edu/probability/chapter/topic-2-4/">expected value</ref> of <m>X</m> is
       <me>E(X) = v_1 \cdot p_1 + v_2 \cdot p_2 + v_3 \cdot p_3 ... = \sum_{i} v_i \cdot p_i</me>
