            Hint
**********************************************-->
<hint name="helpSection"><title>Worked Example</title>



<p>Here is a similar worked example:</p> 
<example newNameSpace>
<p><em>You hold one ticket to a raffle that has the following payouts:</em></p>

<p><em>You will win <m>\$ 10</m> with probability <m>$p10</m></em></p>
<p><em>You will win <m>\$ 5</m> with probability <m>$p5</m></em> </p>
<p><em>You will win <m>\$ 2</m> with probability <m>$p2</m></em></p>
<p><em>You will win <m>\$ 1</m> with probability <m>$p1</m></em></p>

<setup>
  <math name="p10" displayDecimals="2">0.09</math>
  <math name="p5" displayDecimals="2">0.17</math>
  <math name="p2" displayDecimals="2">0.22</math>
  <math name="p1" simplify displayDecimals="2" padZeros>1 - $p10 - $p5 - $p2</math>
  <math name="expectedValue" displayDecimals="2" padZeros>10$p10 + 5$p5 + 2$p2 + $p1</math>
</setup>

<p><alert><em>Solution.</em></alert></p>
<p>Using the <ref uri="https://open.lib.umn.edu/probability/chapter/topic-2-4/">expected value formula</ref>, we have
  <md>
    <mrow>E(X) \amp= v_1 \cdot p_1 + v_2 \cdot p_2 + v_3 \cdot p_3 ... = \sum_{i} v_i \cdot p_i \amp\text{general formula}</mrow>
    <mrow>E(X) \amp = $expectedValue \amp\text{substitute known information}</mrow>
    <mrow>\amp= $expectedValue{simplify} \amp\text{simplify}</mrow>
  </md>

</p>
  
</example>

<p><em>How to check</em>: Ask yourself whether the dollar value you computed seems reasonable considering the given probabilities? Make sure your answer is a value between <m>1</m> and <m>10</m>, because the expected value of the winnings cannot be greater than the maximum or minimum value that it is possible to win.</p>
  </hint>

<!--*********************************************
            Solution
**********************************************-->  
<solution>
<p>Using the <ref uri="https://open.lib.umn.edu/probability/chapter/topic-2-4/">expected value formula</ref>, we have
  <md>
    <mrow>E(X) \amp= v_1 \cdot p_1 + v_2 \cdot p_2 + v_3 \cdot p_3 ... = \sum_{i} v_i \cdot p_i \amp\text{general formula}</mrow>
    <mrow>E(X) \amp = $expectedValue \amp\text{substitute known information}</mrow>
    <mrow>\amp= $expectedValue{simplify} \amp\text{simplify}</mrow>
  </md>

</p>
</solution>
</problem>

